    "McDowell, for instance, states: 'If one attempted to reduce one's conception of what virtue requires to a set of rules, then, however subtle and thoughtful one was in drawing up the code, cases would inevitably turn up in which a mechanical application of the rules would strike one as wrong' (McDowell, 1979, p. 337).",
    "Why is the moral domain such that it cannot be captured in a finite set of rules, even in principle?",
